_refine.details                                  
;DUE TO THE PRESENCE OF ORTHORHOMBIC PSEUDOSYMMETRY, THE TEST SET OF REFLECTIONS WERE CHOSEN IN P212121 AND THEN EXPANDED TO COVER THE MONOCLINIC SPACE GROUP. DATA WERE FOUND TO BE NEAR- PERFECTLY TWINNED AND WERE THEREFORE TREATED AS PERFECTLY TWINNED. NCS RESTRAINTS WERE APPLIED DURING REFINEMENT WITH POSITIONAL RESTRAINTS OF 30 KCAL/MOL-A**2 (300 INITIALLY) AND B-FACTOR TARGET SIGMA OF 2
;
