_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 2C4P 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;CATALYZES THE COVALENT ATTACHMENT OF UBIQUITIN TO OTHER
 PROTEINS. MEDIATES THE SELECTIVE DEGRADATION OF SHORT-LIVED
 AND ABNORMAL PROTEINS. FUNCTIONS IN THE E6/E6-AP-INDUCED
 UBIQUITINATION OF P53/TP53.
;
_pdbx_entry_details.source_details           ? 
_pdbx_entry_details.nonpolymer_details       ? 
_pdbx_entry_details.sequence_details         
;RESIDUES FOR WHICH INSUFFICIENT DENSITY WAS OBSERVED FOR
SIDECHAINS WERE TRUNCATED TO ALANINES. THE PROTEIN WAS
TAGGED WITH A HIS6-TAG THAT WAS NEVER CLEAVED FROM THE
PROTEIN. THEREFORE, IN ADDITION TO THE RGS SEQUENCE
PRECEDING THE UNIPROT UBCH5A SEQUENCE, THE FOLLOWING
RESIDUES WERE PRESENT IN THE STRUCTURE, BUT NOT LOCATED
IN THE ELECTRON DENSITY MAPS,PRESUMABLY DUE TO DISORDER:
MKHHHHHHPMSGLVP
;
_pdbx_entry_details.has_ligand_of_interest   ? 
